<slide label="p1-pretext-what-is-it">
  <title>Part I: What Is PreTeXt?</title>

  <p>
    PreTeXt is an open-source authoring system for writing structured, accessible, and interactive educational materials.
  </p>

  <dl pause="no">
    <li>
      <title>Write once, publish everywhere</title>
      <p>Web, PDF, ePub, large print, and Braille from a single source.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <title>Pedagogy-aware structure</title>
      <p>Examples, exercises, definitions, and cross-references are first-class objects.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <title>Accessibility by design</title>
      <p>Screen-reader friendly, responsive layouts, and dark/light modes.</p>
    </li>
  </dl>

  <p>
    The key shift is that PreTeXt handles structure and presentation‚Äîso authors can focus on teaching.
  </p>
</slide>


		<slide label="p1-pretext-what-is-it">
			<title>
				<line>Part I: PreTeXt - What is PreTeXt?</line>
			</title>

			<p>
				PreTeXt is an open-source authoring language designed for writing textbooks, articles, lecture notes, and course materials.
			</p>
			<dl pause="no">
				<li>
					<title>‚ú¶ <em>Write once, publish everywhere</em></title>
					<p>
						From one source you can produce web, PDF, ePub, and Braille versions.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<title>‚ú¶ <em>Built-in Interactive Components:</em></title>
					<p>
						Supplement narrative with interactive reading questions, coding tasks, or visualization tools.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<title>‚ú¶ <em>Accessibility Out of the Box:</em></title>
					<p>
						PreTeXt is Screen-Reader Friendly and supports Braille, Large Print, and Dark/Light Mode.
					</p>
				</li>
			</dl>
			<p>
				Whether you want a polished textbook, an online &amp; interactive research hub, or just clean online lecture notes, PreTeXt is ready for just about any workflow.
			</p>
		</slide>

