		<slide label="p2-why-write-a-book">
			<title>Why Write a New Book?</title>

			<p>
				Every instructor teaching undergraduate mathematics faces the same challenge:
				finding a text that balances clarity, rigor, and accessibility.
			</p>

			<ul pause="no">
				<li>Many commercial texts are expensive and overly formal.</li>
				<li>Free online notes exist, but often lack structure or interactivity.</li>
				<li>I wanted something approachable ‚Äî conversational, visually clear, and ready for digital classrooms.</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				So I decided to write the book I always wanted to teach from.
			</p>

			<p>
				The goal is to make this book a model for how open, interactive materials can evolve within a department.
			</p>
		</slide>

<slide label="p2-design-philosophy">
  <title>Student-Centered Design Principles</title>

  <ul pause="no">
    <li>Conversational, instructor-like tone</li>
    <li>Short narrative blocks‚Äîno walls of text</li>
    <li>Frequent, low-stakes reflection points</li>
    <li>Visualizations embedded at moments of confusion</li>
    <li>Optional audio narration for accessibility</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    The goal is not more interaction‚Äîbut better-timed interaction.
  </p>
</slide>


		<slide label="p2-design-philosphy-features">
			<title>Design Philosophy &amp; Features</title>

			<p>
				One of the major advantages of authoring in PreTeXt is how easily interactive components integrate into the flow of the book.
			</p>

			<ul pause="no">
				<li>Embedded exercises with automatic feedback (via Runestone or WeBWorK).</li>
				<li>Audio narration and accessibility extensions for broader reach.</li>
				<li>Dynamic visualizations for slope fields, phase lines, and numerical approximations.</li>
				<li>Expandable ‚Äúcheck your understanding‚Äù questions built right into the narrative.</li>
				<li>Flexible integration with Jupyter or Sage for symbolic computation examples.</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				Students can read, compute, and explore ‚Äî all in one place.
			</p>
		</slide>

